  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nDealers are in maximum pain territory with SPX sitting right at the -45.9B gamma wall at 6765, forcing aggressive long hedging that amplifies any downside momentum. The massive negative gamma surge (-31% in 1min, -72% in 5min) indicates heavy put buying or call selling just hit the tape, creating a dangerous feedback loop where dealers must chase moves in the same direction. With spot trapped between thick negative gamma walls from 6750-6770 and only modest positive gamma resistance at 6800, expect violent whipsaws with any break below 6750 triggering accelerated selling into the 6430 flip level.\n\n**Bottom line:** Dealers are forced to sell any dip, making moves lower fast and nasty.",
